President Biden has declared a state of emergency in Florida due to the impact of Tropical Storm Elsa. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts to assist the local population in alleviating hardship and suffering caused by the storm. FEMA is authorized to provide equipment and resources as needed, and will provide 75 percent federal funding for emergency protective measures such as evacuation and shelter support. Kevin A. Wallace has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.